{{Infobox film | name = Fire Monsters Against the Son of Hercules | image = Maciste-contro-i-mostri-italian-movie-poster-md.jpg | alt = | caption = Italian film poster | film name = <!-- {{Infobox name module|language|title}} or {{Infobox name module|title}} --> | director = [[Guido Malatesta]] | producer = {{plainlist|*Giorgio Marzelli * Alfio Quattrini{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=57}}}} | writer = | screenplay = {{plainlist|*Arpad DeRiso *Guido Malatesta{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=57}}}} | based on = <!-- {{Based on|title of the original work|creator of the original work|additional creator(s), if necessary}} --> | starring = {{plainlist|*[[Reg Lewis]] *[[Margaret Lee (English actress)|Margaret Lee]] *[[Luciano Marin]]}} | narrator = | music = {{plainlist|*Guido Robuschi * Gian Stellari{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=58}}}} | cinematography = Giuseppe La Torre{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=57}} | editing = | production companies = {{plainlist|*Euro International *Caserbib}} | distributor = | released = {{Film date|df=yes|1962|4|25|Italy}} | runtime = 82 minutes{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=58}} | country = {{plainlist|*Italy *Yugoslavia{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=58}}}} | language = | budget = | gross = }}
'''''Fire Monsters Against the Son of Hercules''''' ({{lang-it|Maciste contro i mostri}}) is a 1962 film directed by [[Guido Malatesta]] that was filmed in Yugoslavia and Italy.
== Plot summary == Set in the Ice Age, a nomadic tribe of sun worshippers reach an area they decide to settle in. When Idar and Rhia, a young couple of the tribe come across a water monster, the monster is killed by [[Maciste]] with a spear. The two ask Maciste to join their tribe but Maciste explains he has a destiny to fulfill of righting wrongs and must leave.
Soon afterwards a cave dwelling tribe of moon worshippers led by Fuwan attack the village and carry off the sun worshipper's women. Maciste returns to the sun worshippers and enter the moon worshipper's underground city through a river. There he discovers Moah, whose father and brother who had formerly led the tribe were murdered by Fuwan and wishes to take Moah. Moah explains that the moon worshippers will sacrifice the captured women in a celebration of the full moon that night.
Maciste passes through an underwater tunnel, defeats the three headed hydra that lives there and is able to eliminate the guards to the entrance and remove the stone gate to the entrance letting the vengeful sun worshippers in. The women are freed but Maciste destroys their path to the surface once they have left and is captured by the moon worshippers who bury him, and later Moah in the earth so the worms may eat their bodies. They are saved by a volcanic eruption that sets them free and kills a large portion of the moon worshippers.
Seeking revenge, the moon worshippers make a pact with a tribe of cannibals to attack the sun worshippers. The combined forces are defeated by the sun worshippers and Maciste. Moah joins Maciste on his future journeys.
== Cast == *[[Reg Lewis (bodybuilder)|Reg Lewis]] as [[Maciste|Maciste/ Maxus]] *[[Margaret Lee (British actress)|Margaret Lee]] as Moah *[[Luciano Marin]] as Idar son of Dorak *[[Andrea Aureli]] as Rhia *[[Birgit Bergen]] as Agmir *[[Nello Pazzafini]] as Fuwan *[[Miria Kent]] as Woman of the Sun *[[Fulvia Gasser]] as Woman of the Sun *[[Rocco Spataro]] as Dorak *[[Ivan Pengow]] as Gamel the Fire Keeper
==Production== ''Fire Monsters Against the Son of Hercules'' was a co-production between Italy's Euro International Film and Yugoslavia's Caserbib.{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=58}} The film was shot at Incir De Paolis Studios in Rome and on location in the caves of [[Ljublijana]] in [[Slovenia]].{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=58}}
In the English-language version, Maciste is called "Maxus", referring to him as a son of Hercules.{{sfn|Della Casa|Giusti|2013|p=211}}{{sfn|Hughes|2011|p=19}} Maciste's name is changed to Maxus, so whenever Maxus' name is mentioned, a different higher-registered voice adds the dubbed name.{{sfn|Hughes|2011|p=19}}{{sfn|Hughes|2011|p=20}}
==Release== The film was released in Italy on 25 April 1962.{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=58}} It was also released as ''Colossus of the Stone Age'' in England.{{sfn|Kinnard|Crnkovich|2017|p=58}}{{sfn|Della Casa|Giusti|2013|p=211}}
==Reception== In his book on Italian cinema, Howard Hughes discussed the English-language dub of the film, declaring it "probably the worst dubbing job of all time".{{sfn|Hughes|2011|p=19}}
